  "prompt": "How much time does Deloitte generally takes to get back after interview?",
  "response": "The time it takes for Deloitte to get back to you after an interview can vary depending on several factors, including the role, location, and stage of the hiring process. However, here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **First Round Interviews**: If you've completed a first-round interview, Deloitte typically takes **1-2 weeks** to provide feedback or inform you about the next steps.\n\n2. **Final Round Interviews**: After a final-round interview, the decision-making process might take **2-4 weeks**, as the team often needs time to deliberate and finalize their choice.\n\n3. **Exceptions**: In some cases, it could take longer, especially if there are multiple candidates, internal approvals, or delays in the hiring process.\n\n4. **Follow-Up**: If you haven\u2019t heard back within the expected timeframe, it\u2019s appropriate to send a polite follow-up email to your recruiter or HR contact to inquire about the status of your application.\n\nKeep in mind that the timeline can vary, so patience is key while waiting for a response.",
